column12: Measurement condition : Altered; Clear  No Precipitation  Calm Wind Swirling/Variable
column13: New bridge construction downstream of gauge pillar in right side of channel riprap built up on both banks. Construction is d/s of existing bridge over the river. Otherwise clear channel.
column14: Manned boat ADCP measurement at boat launch roughly 200m d/s of gauge. Good quality measurement water was calm good SNR and GPS. Some moving bed found.  @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller 2016) 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ Removed damaged ott cabling from gauge house so it is less cluttered. Left outside of shelter on ground coiled up. Labeled temp line and perm line as it was unclear which was which. TEMP LINE STILL BEING USED I THINK?! Couldn't get sensor to reset. Purged temp line again. Observed bubbles on temp line. Then connected perm line  and purged Better bubbles observed closer to shore. Attempted to hook up perm line again. Finally perm line settled out. MMT conducted before sensor calibration - applied found SRC to the MGH. ADCP by Moving Boat

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Clear  Light Rain
column13: CIC with ongoing bridge construction downstream.
column14: Good quality under-ice mmt. Encountered very high pressure pocket in centre of channel - water shot 10ft out of hole blew auger out along with it. Ice thickness significantly less in that area.  @ Uncertainty: ISO method 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ FIrst DWL/comparison done using BM 09-1 (with a GC of -0.006m found today). Second comparison done using TBM 21-2 (no GC stable). switching reference point @ 1400. Large SRC found to both sensors completed circuit twice to confirm results and then completed a third partial circuit from today's turning point into a different DWL hole just to ensure elevation of ice/water surface was consistent throughout x-section and it was. Reset sensors following visit. Used DWL values (from BM 09-1) with GC of -0.006m applied (found today).  Mid-section
GC: -0.006 HG: 0.990 Found (FD)

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Partly Cloudy  No Precipitation  Calm Wind
column14: 108 m3/s REPRESENTED ONLY 60% OF THE CHANNEL WIDTH DUE TO EQUIPMENT FAILURE. USING THE 01/22 MMT TO COMPARE 0M - 100M (RIGHT BANK SIDE) IT APPEARS AS THOUGH APPROX 35 M3/S MAY HAVE BEEN MISSED. (ROUNDED EACH PANEL DOWN TO ACCOUNT FOR REDUCTION IN FLOW BETWEEN 01/22 AND 02/24. THIS RESULTS IN AN AGGREGATED MMT (ESTIMATE) DISCHARGE OF 144m3/S  **GC REMOVED FOLLOWING BM TIE RESULTS IN 2021** 108 m^3/s measured in 60% of channel. 40% unmeasured due to equipment failure. Nearly a meter of ice in last 90m of river with a lot of slush in the holes. Further measurement review required prior to publication of measurement data.   Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of -0.066 and Gauge Correction of -0.005 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 1.735 First water level invalid. DO NOT USE FOR SRC OR MGH Mid-section
